# Global feature sync (AR-local)

Shared agent plumbing must stay aligned with the public global repo: **https://github.com/yanniedog/cursor-global-workflow**

Local clone (typical): `~/code/cursor-global-workflow` or `%USERPROFILE%\code\cursor-global-workflow`.

## Canonical features (mirror on change)

| Piece | AR-local path | Global path |
|-------|---------------|-------------|
| Chief | `.cursor/skills/chief-agent/` | `skills/chief-agent/` |
| Orchestrator | `.cursor/skills/workflow-orchestrator/` | `skills/workflow-orchestrator/` |
| Browser QA | `.cursor/skills/deep-browser-explore/` | `skills/deep-browser-explore/` |
| Auditor | `.cursor/skills/agent-auditor/` | `skills/agent-auditor/` |
| Ship bar (AR-local) | `wait_for_bots.mjs`, `ship_closeout_strict.py`, `scripts/chief-scan.mjs`, `scripts/pr-bot-feedback-check.mjs`, `scripts/agent-auditor-scan.mjs`, `scripts/lib/bot-wait-config.mjs`, `scripts/lib/bot-wait-presence.mjs`, `scripts/lib/agent-auditor-lib.mjs` | `scripts/` (Node equivalents; see global `package.json`) |
| Hooks | `.cursor/hooks/auditor-watch.mjs`, `.cursor/hooks/orchestrator-remind.mjs` | `hooks/` |
| Shared rules | `.cursor/rules/chief-agent-always.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/workflow-orchestrator-always.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/agent-auditor-always.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/no-early-stop-after-pr.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/pr-review-bot-replies.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/respond-to-each-review-comment.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/multiagent-modularity.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/workflow-rules-never-overridden.mdc` | `rules/` |

Also mirror edits under `~/.cursor/skills/` or `~/.cursor/workflow-scripts/` when those are the canonical copies you changed.

## Before done on a PR that touches the table

1. Apply the same change in `cursor-global-workflow` (generalize project-specific paths).
2. Scrub private hostnames, paths, and secrets.
3. Push global `main`; record global commit SHA in the AR-local PR body.
4. Do **not** bundle global-only policy with unrelated feature work — use `agent/global-feature-sync-policy-*` or a dedicated sync commit.

Chief: if a worker edits listed paths, assign sync in the **same PR cycle** or spawn a sync subagent before merge.

Orchestrator: **global mirror check** before `gh pr merge` when the PR diff includes any row above.

## Invoke

**"sync global workflow"** — mirror listed paths to `cursor-global-workflow`, push, report SHA.
